00:01:07.640 --> 00:01:09.700 align:middle line:90%
Thank you, Corinne.

00:01:09.700 --> 00:01:13.040 align:middle line:84%
>> I want to talk about the most
practical chapter in the book--

00:01:13.040 --> 00:01:13.840 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:01:13.840 --> 00:01:15.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Which is Chapter 6.

00:01:15.730 --> 00:01:17.800 align:middle line:90%
And you call it Grown Up Love.

00:01:17.800 --> 00:01:20.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Grown Ups in Love, yeah.

00:01:20.750 --> 00:01:23.380 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, it's wonderful to
talk about the theory of love,

00:01:23.380 --> 00:01:29.440 align:middle line:84%
but this chapter actually
gets down to beyond or before

00:01:29.440 --> 00:01:35.080 align:middle line:84%
the spiritual to what mainly
makes people tick and what do

00:01:35.080 --> 00:01:36.455 align:middle line:90%
they want.

00:01:36.455 --> 00:01:38.830 align:middle line:10%
>> In that chapter, I quote
a woman whose lectures I used

00:01:38.830 --> 00:01:42.550 align:middle line:10%
to hear a lot in Los Angeles
named Pat Allen, Dr. Pat Allen.

00:01:42.550 --> 00:01:44.290 align:middle line:84%
She's a psychotherapist
and an author.

00:01:44.290 --> 00:01:49.990 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of her work is based
on the theories of Carl Jung.

00:01:49.990 --> 00:01:52.240 align:middle line:84%
And she said a few
things that really

00:01:52.240 --> 00:01:53.800 align:middle line:90%
affected me deeply in my life.

00:01:53.800 --> 00:01:57.160 align:middle line:84%
And one was that she claims
that a man's greatest psychic

00:01:57.160 --> 00:01:59.770 align:middle line:84%
need is to have his
thoughts respected.

00:01:59.770 --> 00:02:01.780 align:middle line:84%
And a woman's
greatest psychic need

00:02:01.780 --> 00:02:04.210 align:middle line:84%
is to have her
feelings cherished.

00:02:04.210 --> 00:02:07.360 align:middle line:84%
And I think
sometimes women focus

00:02:07.360 --> 00:02:10.509 align:middle line:84%
on what we think more
than focus on how we feel.

00:02:10.509 --> 00:02:12.220 align:middle line:84%
And also I think
sometimes we ask men

00:02:12.220 --> 00:02:14.770 align:middle line:84%
how they feel more
than what they think

00:02:14.770 --> 00:02:20.620 align:middle line:84%
in ways that set all
of us up for behavior

00:02:20.620 --> 00:02:24.920 align:middle line:84%
and experience that is less than
the most that we're capable of.

00:02:24.920 --> 00:02:29.650 align:middle line:84%
So I deal with that theory
of hers in that chapter.

00:02:29.650 --> 00:02:31.565 align:middle line:84%
>> You said that was
a revelation for you.

00:02:31.565 --> 00:02:33.190 align:middle line:84%
>> It was a bit of
a revelation for me,

00:02:33.190 --> 00:02:35.500 align:middle line:84%
because I'm very much
of the generation--

00:02:35.500 --> 00:02:38.920 align:middle line:84%
I became what in
Carl Jung theories is

00:02:38.920 --> 00:02:40.630 align:middle line:90%
called the father's daughter.

00:02:40.630 --> 00:02:43.750 align:middle line:84%
What that means is this--
what Pat Allen suggests

00:02:43.750 --> 00:02:47.650 align:middle line:84%
is that when my generation
was around puberty,

00:02:47.650 --> 00:02:49.720 align:middle line:84%
our parents made
some big mistakes

00:02:49.720 --> 00:02:53.410 align:middle line:84%
in a psychological sense
with the best of intentions.

00:02:53.410 --> 00:02:55.690 align:middle line:84%
And that is that
just as young men

00:02:55.690 --> 00:02:58.090 align:middle line:84%
used to go-- and still in
some Indigenous cultures

00:02:58.090 --> 00:02:59.200 align:middle line:90%
go through puberty rites.

00:02:59.200 --> 00:03:01.120 align:middle line:84%
Even today, the bar
mitzvah is basically

00:03:01.120 --> 00:03:04.060 align:middle line:84%
a puberty right where there is
a ceremonial and ritualistic

00:03:04.060 --> 00:03:06.880 align:middle line:84%
transformation from
boyhood to manhood.

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:10.050 align:middle line:84%
And basically, just
as in the bar mitzvah,

00:03:10.050 --> 00:03:12.340 align:middle line:84%
the real communication to
the community, to the boy,

00:03:12.340 --> 00:03:14.860 align:middle line:84%
to his mother is that
he is a boy no longer.

00:03:14.860 --> 00:03:16.570 align:middle line:90%
He is now a man.

00:03:16.570 --> 00:03:18.970 align:middle line:84%
And the psychological
imperative there for the mother

00:03:18.970 --> 00:03:21.640 align:middle line:84%
is to stop coddling his
feelings and to start

00:03:21.640 --> 00:03:25.030 align:middle line:84%
respecting his choices, showing
respect for his choices.

00:03:25.030 --> 00:03:27.970 align:middle line:84%
Now in our generation, a
lot of that went backwards.

00:03:27.970 --> 00:03:30.220 align:middle line:84%
And women thought that they
were doing the right thing

00:03:30.220 --> 00:03:33.070 align:middle line:84%
helping men stay in touch with
their feminine by coddling

00:03:33.070 --> 00:03:36.320 align:middle line:84%
an adolescent boy and older,
coddling his feelings.

00:03:36.320 --> 00:03:37.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Cutting him too much slack?

00:03:37.630 --> 00:03:39.310 align:middle line:90%
>> In a way, yes.

00:03:39.310 --> 00:03:41.920 align:middle line:84%
And fathers, often with
the best of intentions,

00:03:41.920 --> 00:03:44.380 align:middle line:84%
made the opposite mistake
with their daughters.

00:03:44.380 --> 00:03:47.650 align:middle line:84%
So that we would come home
at adolescence, at puberty,

00:03:47.650 --> 00:03:51.970 align:middle line:90%
having made an A plus in--

00:03:51.970 --> 00:03:54.640 align:middle line:84%
I don't know--
something like science.

00:03:54.640 --> 00:03:57.273 align:middle line:84%
And so the father, once again
with the best of intentions,

00:03:57.273 --> 00:03:58.690 align:middle line:84%
slaps us on the
back and says, you

00:03:58.690 --> 00:04:00.700 align:middle line:90%
can do as good as any boy can.

00:04:00.700 --> 00:04:05.080 align:middle line:84%
Now, we got some really
unfortunate messages there.

00:04:05.080 --> 00:04:09.910 align:middle line:84%
The girl, in that case, has
led to believe that achieving

00:04:09.910 --> 00:04:13.630 align:middle line:84%
something, achieving more--
if I only achieve more--

00:04:13.630 --> 00:04:17.140 align:middle line:84%
that will gain me love
from the men in my life.

00:04:17.140 --> 00:04:19.450 align:middle line:84%
And many of us learned,
very painfully,

00:04:19.450 --> 00:04:21.620 align:middle line:90%
that that's simply not true.

00:04:21.620 --> 00:04:25.060 align:middle line:10%
So what started to happen
was this really neurotic

00:04:25.060 --> 00:04:27.490 align:middle line:10%
interaction between
grown men and women,

00:04:27.490 --> 00:04:30.670 align:middle line:10%
really stuck at adolescence,
with the message of the man

00:04:30.670 --> 00:04:33.910 align:middle line:10%
tending to be my mother
still loved me when I acted

00:04:33.910 --> 00:04:35.770 align:middle line:10%
like an idiot, why don't you?

00:04:35.770 --> 00:04:38.320 align:middle line:84%
And the response is because
I'm not your mother.

00:04:38.320 --> 00:04:39.160 align:middle line:90%
>> You said--

00:04:39.160 --> 00:04:40.327 align:middle line:90%
>> Excuse me, just a moment.

00:04:40.327 --> 00:04:42.520 align:middle line:84%
And then the message to
the man from the woman

00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:45.520 align:middle line:84%
is my father loved me when I
achieved more and more, why

00:04:45.520 --> 00:04:47.320 align:middle line:90%
doesn't that earn your love?

00:04:47.320 --> 00:04:50.470 align:middle line:84%
And the response is because
I'm not your father.

00:04:50.470 --> 00:04:54.910 align:middle line:84%
So we have to make a leap
across that great divide

00:04:54.910 --> 00:04:58.340 align:middle line:84%
to become women who respect
the man for his decisions

00:04:58.340 --> 00:05:02.380 align:middle line:84%
and his choices and to love
a woman for her feelings

00:05:02.380 --> 00:05:05.560 align:middle line:84%
and to put behind us that more
immature interaction where

00:05:05.560 --> 00:05:07.992 align:middle line:84%
we got stuck, really, in the
dynamic with our parents.

00:05:07.992 --> 00:05:09.700 align:middle line:84%
So thank you for
letting me just complete

00:05:09.700 --> 00:05:10.580 align:middle line:90%
the other side of that.

00:05:10.580 --> 00:05:11.380 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:05:11.380 --> 00:05:14.770 align:middle line:84%
>> No, I think it's a very
important thought because I

00:05:14.770 --> 00:05:17.510 align:middle line:84%
also was brought up
along those lines.

00:05:17.510 --> 00:05:18.490 align:middle line:90%
You can do anything.

00:05:18.490 --> 00:05:19.780 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, which we can.

00:05:19.780 --> 00:05:20.740 align:middle line:84%
And it's not like we
want to go backwards.

00:05:20.740 --> 00:05:23.140 align:middle line:84%
>> And you're never suggesting
not to do everything.

00:05:23.140 --> 00:05:24.190 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, absolutely not.

00:05:24.190 --> 00:05:26.410 align:middle line:84%
>> But that's not what
gets the man's attention.

00:05:26.410 --> 00:05:28.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, what I'm suggesting
is that the psychological

00:05:28.360 --> 00:05:28.960 align:middle line:90%
dynamic--

00:05:28.960 --> 00:05:30.440 align:middle line:90%
you're a woman in the workplace.

00:05:30.440 --> 00:05:31.730 align:middle line:90%
I'm a woman in the workplace.

00:05:31.730 --> 00:05:33.790 align:middle line:84%
There's a certain
psychological dynamic

00:05:33.790 --> 00:05:36.640 align:middle line:84%
which is appropriate here
and which is valid here.

00:05:36.640 --> 00:05:38.530 align:middle line:84%
But it's basically
a masculine dynamic.

00:05:38.530 --> 00:05:41.993 align:middle line:84%
And I think all men and women
are masculine and feminine.

00:05:41.993 --> 00:05:43.660 align:middle line:84%
So I'm glad that you
and I have a chance

00:05:43.660 --> 00:05:47.530 align:middle line:84%
to experience our masculine
dynamic, going out, doing,

00:05:47.530 --> 00:05:48.400 align:middle line:90%
achieving.

00:05:48.400 --> 00:05:49.750 align:middle line:84%
Just as it's wonderful
for men to be

00:05:49.750 --> 00:05:51.370 align:middle line:84%
in touch with their
feelings and experience

00:05:51.370 --> 00:05:53.380 align:middle line:84%
their feminine dynamic
that they can be passive

00:05:53.380 --> 00:05:54.820 align:middle line:90%
and they can be receptive.

00:05:54.820 --> 00:05:57.520 align:middle line:84%
However, let's be really
clear when it comes--

00:05:57.520 --> 00:05:59.410 align:middle line:84%
well, not only in
heterosexual relationships,

00:05:59.410 --> 00:06:01.285 align:middle line:84%
because I think this
dynamic is the same even

00:06:01.285 --> 00:06:03.910 align:middle line:84%
in gay relationships-- when
it comes to romantic love,

00:06:03.910 --> 00:06:05.570 align:middle line:90%
it's a different dynamic.

00:06:05.570 --> 00:06:08.530 align:middle line:84%
So the same psychological
dynamic that makes you

00:06:08.530 --> 00:06:11.510 align:middle line:84%
and me, in some cases,
successful in our careers,

00:06:11.510 --> 00:06:14.270 align:middle line:84%
if we want to be successful
in romantic relationships,

00:06:14.270 --> 00:06:16.490 align:middle line:84%
we have to move into a
different part of the brain

00:06:16.490 --> 00:06:18.123 align:middle line:84%
into a different
part of the soul.

00:06:18.123 --> 00:06:19.540 align:middle line:84%
You know, and that
makes it sense.

00:06:19.540 --> 00:06:20.390 align:middle line:90%
There's yin and yang.

00:06:20.390 --> 00:06:21.848 align:middle line:84%
There's the active
and the passive.

00:06:21.848 --> 00:06:23.700 align:middle line:84%
There's the masculine
and the feminine.

00:06:23.700 --> 00:06:24.990 align:middle line:90%
And they're different.

00:06:24.990 --> 00:06:25.790 align:middle line:90%
And that's good.

00:06:25.790 --> 00:06:28.280 align:middle line:84%
Those are two
parts of ourselves.

00:06:28.280 --> 00:06:31.970 align:middle line:84%
>> So women have been attracting
these men who are still

00:06:31.970 --> 00:06:35.570 align:middle line:84%
mama's boys, who seem to want
to express their feelings all

00:06:35.570 --> 00:06:36.830 align:middle line:90%
the time.

00:06:36.830 --> 00:06:39.860 align:middle line:84%
And they're attracted
to us because we

00:06:39.860 --> 00:06:42.020 align:middle line:84%
seem to be pretty
powerful and achievers.

00:06:42.020 --> 00:06:43.737 align:middle line:84%
>> Sometimes that's
one of the ways.

00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:46.070 align:middle line:84%
>> We get bored with them,
because we really want a man.

00:06:46.070 --> 00:06:46.945 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, that's right.

00:06:46.945 --> 00:06:50.800 align:middle line:84%
>> We've forgotten our genetic
imprinting, haven't we?

00:06:50.800 --> 00:06:53.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think there's
some genetic imprinting here.

00:06:53.050 --> 00:06:54.640 align:middle line:84%
And we need to be so
careful because we

00:06:54.640 --> 00:06:56.740 align:middle line:84%
don't want to sound retro and
we don't want a sound backlash.

00:06:56.740 --> 00:06:57.520 align:middle line:90%
And we don't want to--

00:06:57.520 --> 00:06:58.690 align:middle line:84%
>> You can do anything
you want on this show.

00:06:58.690 --> 00:07:00.400 align:middle line:90%
>> No, I really do want to.

00:07:00.400 --> 00:07:03.010 align:middle line:84%
I mean I think it's important
not to be suggesting that we're

00:07:03.010 --> 00:07:05.230 align:middle line:84%
supposed to go back 30 or
40 years because that's not

00:07:05.230 --> 00:07:06.460 align:middle line:90%
what I'm saying.

00:07:06.460 --> 00:07:10.680 align:middle line:84%
I'm simply saying that there
is a way in which, I think,

00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:12.430 align:middle line:84%
men with the men's
movement, for instance,

00:07:12.430 --> 00:07:13.805 align:middle line:84%
now are realizing
that, yes, they

00:07:13.805 --> 00:07:15.340 align:middle line:84%
got in touch with
their feminine,

00:07:15.340 --> 00:07:17.530 align:middle line:84%
but sometimes at the
expense of their masculine.

00:07:17.530 --> 00:07:19.447 align:middle line:84%
And you and I got in
touch with our masculine,

00:07:19.447 --> 00:07:21.490 align:middle line:84%
but sometimes at the
expense of our feminine.

00:07:21.490 --> 00:07:23.830 align:middle line:84%
And it's just a balancing
that's occurring right now.

00:07:23.830 --> 00:07:25.930 align:middle line:84%
Once again, we don't want
to give up the strides,

00:07:25.930 --> 00:07:29.240 align:middle line:84%
but we want to move into a
space of honoring the mystery,

00:07:29.240 --> 00:07:30.040 align:middle line:90%
for instance.

00:07:30.040 --> 00:07:31.900 align:middle line:84%
I think that we have
demystified love

00:07:31.900 --> 00:07:34.270 align:middle line:90%
in the name of mental health.

00:07:34.270 --> 00:07:35.920 align:middle line:90%
You know, love is a mystery.

00:07:35.920 --> 00:07:37.400 align:middle line:90%
And it's very fragile.

00:07:37.400 --> 00:07:41.320 align:middle line:84%
And you can't define
it all the time.

00:07:41.320 --> 00:07:44.160 align:middle line:84%
You know, Goethe once said
to analyze is to murder.

00:07:44.160 --> 00:07:47.590 align:middle line:84%
There is a way in which the
deepest experience of romance,

00:07:47.590 --> 00:07:49.360 align:middle line:90%
it's a mystery.

00:07:49.360 --> 00:07:52.430 align:middle line:84%
It's not something that you
can just set up a formula

00:07:52.430 --> 00:07:53.770 align:middle line:90%
and then you'll have it.

00:07:53.770 --> 00:07:55.700 align:middle line:84%
What you can do is
set up a temple.

00:07:55.700 --> 00:07:59.350 align:middle line:84%
What you can do is create
fertile ground, fertile ground

00:07:59.350 --> 00:08:02.830 align:middle line:90%
for that mystery to unfold.

00:08:02.830 --> 00:08:06.093 align:middle line:84%
And then if it does, you can
honor it and you can tend it.

00:08:06.093 --> 00:08:07.510 align:middle line:84%
And if it doesn't,
you can realize

00:08:07.510 --> 00:08:10.318 align:middle line:84%
that even it's not being there,
it's part of a sacred journey

00:08:10.318 --> 00:08:12.610 align:middle line:84%
so that at least you're asking
the right questions that

00:08:12.610 --> 00:08:14.542 align:middle line:90%
will lead you back to it.

00:08:14.542 --> 00:08:15.500 align:middle line:90%
That's what I'm saying.

00:08:15.500 --> 00:08:18.850 align:middle line:84%
I'm saying that the masculine
mind is the externally focused

00:08:18.850 --> 00:08:20.650 align:middle line:90%
mind in men and in women.

00:08:20.650 --> 00:08:23.410 align:middle line:84%
That has a part to
play, but it's only half

00:08:23.410 --> 00:08:24.850 align:middle line:90%
of the creative existence.

00:08:24.850 --> 00:08:27.190 align:middle line:84%
And it's not the part of
the mind that can really

00:08:27.190 --> 00:08:29.590 align:middle line:90%
earn us love or tend to love.

00:08:29.590 --> 00:08:32.760 align:middle line:84%
>> The part of the mind that
earns its love for a woman is

00:08:32.760 --> 00:08:35.080 align:middle line:90%
a man who is a man.

00:08:35.080 --> 00:08:38.020 align:middle line:90%
And yet, we have been, somehow--

00:08:38.020 --> 00:08:42.000 align:middle line:84%
been, somehow we've gotten
drafted, in many cases,

00:08:42.000 --> 00:08:45.510 align:middle line:90%
in becoming a man's mother.

00:08:45.510 --> 00:08:48.070 align:middle line:84%
And it hasn't worked, because
it's really not what we want.

00:08:48.070 --> 00:08:49.120 align:middle line:90%
>> It's not what we want.

00:08:49.120 --> 00:08:51.203 align:middle line:84%
And at the deepest level,
it's not what they want.

00:08:51.203 --> 00:08:53.320 align:middle line:84%
A lot of times women
will say, he left me

00:08:53.320 --> 00:08:54.760 align:middle line:90%
after I did so much for him.

00:08:54.760 --> 00:08:58.810 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes the problem was
that we did too much for him.

00:08:58.810 --> 00:09:01.870 align:middle line:84%
If you're to be a man's
lover or a man's wife,

00:09:01.870 --> 00:09:03.400 align:middle line:90%
you're not his mother.

00:09:03.400 --> 00:09:05.197 align:middle line:90%
And you're not his teacher.

00:09:05.197 --> 00:09:06.280 align:middle line:90%
>> That was another point.

00:09:06.280 --> 00:09:09.400 align:middle line:84%
>> And if you mother a
man or become his teacher,

00:09:09.400 --> 00:09:12.580 align:middle line:84%
what that does is cancel out
