00:17:59.570 --> 00:18:04.700 align:middle line:84%
often, with the men standing
up and apologizing prayerfully

00:18:04.700 --> 00:18:07.700 align:middle line:84%
to the women and the women
standing up and apologizing

00:18:07.700 --> 00:18:09.110 align:middle line:90%
prayerfully to the men.

00:18:09.110 --> 00:18:10.550 align:middle line:90%
Why don't we have a truce?

00:18:10.550 --> 00:18:12.920 align:middle line:84%
Why don't we have amnesty
between the sexes?

00:18:12.920 --> 00:18:14.570 align:middle line:84%
Why don't we just
cancel the debt?

00:18:14.570 --> 00:18:16.430 align:middle line:90%
Everybody's been hurt.

00:18:16.430 --> 00:18:17.660 align:middle line:90%
Men have hurt women.

00:18:17.660 --> 00:18:19.785 align:middle line:90%
Women have hurt men.

00:18:19.785 --> 00:18:20.660 align:middle line:90%
We've been abandoned.

00:18:20.660 --> 00:18:21.493 align:middle line:90%
And we've abandoned.

00:18:21.493 --> 00:18:24.110 align:middle line:84%
Let's just do this huge
group, "I'm really sorry.

00:18:24.110 --> 00:18:25.790 align:middle line:90%
I didn't mean to hurt you."

00:18:25.790 --> 00:18:29.170 align:middle line:84%
That's the only way we can
go on, because otherwise I

00:18:29.170 --> 00:18:30.170 align:middle line:90%
have abandonment issues.

00:18:30.170 --> 00:18:32.420 align:middle line:84%
I'm expecting you to cater
to my abandonment issues

00:18:32.420 --> 00:18:33.770 align:middle line:84%
even though you're not
the one who abandoned me.

00:18:33.770 --> 00:18:35.810 align:middle line:84%
My father was the
one who abandoned me.

00:18:35.810 --> 00:18:36.930 align:middle line:90%
And we're stuck in this.

00:18:36.930 --> 00:18:38.750 align:middle line:90%
Why don't we just start over?

00:18:38.750 --> 00:18:41.300 align:middle line:84%
And what that means is that I
don't want to be stuck forever

00:18:41.300 --> 00:18:43.340 align:middle line:90%
in this "my abandonment issue."

00:18:43.340 --> 00:18:46.040 align:middle line:84%
And I can realize
that if you left,

00:18:46.040 --> 00:18:48.500 align:middle line:84%
you weren't necessarily
abandoning me,

00:18:48.500 --> 00:18:50.750 align:middle line:84%
you were just
turning the corner.

00:18:50.750 --> 00:18:52.760 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't an against me.

00:18:52.760 --> 00:18:55.860 align:middle line:84%
It was a for something that
you felt was your next step.

00:18:55.860 --> 00:18:57.350 align:middle line:90%
So I have a choice here.

00:18:57.350 --> 00:18:59.990 align:middle line:84%
I can either see this
as an abandonment

00:18:59.990 --> 00:19:03.830 align:middle line:84%
or see it in its higher context
which is you met another choice

00:19:03.830 --> 00:19:05.900 align:middle line:90%
and I can respect you for that.

00:19:05.900 --> 00:19:08.570 align:middle line:84%
And if it was the right
choice for you, then it was,

00:19:08.570 --> 00:19:11.360 align:middle line:84%
ultimately, I will see
the right choice for me.

00:19:11.360 --> 00:19:14.350 align:middle line:84%
And if it wasn't the right
choice for you or for me,

00:19:14.350 --> 00:19:16.710 align:middle line:84%
God's still bigger
than your choices.

00:19:16.710 --> 00:19:18.590 align:middle line:84%
So I'm not going to
lose out ultimately,

00:19:18.590 --> 00:19:20.340 align:middle line:84%
because if there's a
level of love here we

00:19:20.340 --> 00:19:23.150 align:middle line:84%
could have exchanged and
you chose not to experience

00:19:23.150 --> 00:19:25.880 align:middle line:84%
with me, somebody else
will because that's where

00:19:25.880 --> 00:19:27.800 align:middle line:90%
my consciousness is right now.

00:19:27.800 --> 00:19:28.830 align:middle line:90%
So I have a choice.

00:19:28.830 --> 00:19:32.570 align:middle line:84%
I don't have to stay in this
rather neurotic and low level

00:19:32.570 --> 00:19:34.180 align:middle line:90%
abandonment issue stuff forever.

00:19:34.180 --> 00:19:38.510 align:middle line:84%
I can move on to a more glorious
sense of myself and of love.

00:19:38.510 --> 00:19:40.700 align:middle line:84%
That's what I've
come to believe.

00:19:40.700 --> 00:19:42.100 align:middle line:90%
>> One of your famous quotes--

00:19:42.100 --> 00:19:44.750 align:middle line:84%
and you used it before
in your last book.

00:19:44.750 --> 00:19:47.430 align:middle line:90%


00:19:47.430 --> 00:19:50.810 align:middle line:84%
And it is "If the train
doesn't stop at your station,

00:19:50.810 --> 00:19:51.685 align:middle line:90%
it's not your train."

00:19:51.685 --> 00:19:52.485 align:middle line:90%
>> I did.

00:19:52.485 --> 00:19:54.480 align:middle line:84%
I used that again in
this book, as I had,

00:19:54.480 --> 00:19:57.600 align:middle line:84%
I think, in "Return to
Love" because so many women

00:19:57.600 --> 00:19:59.670 align:middle line:84%
and men, I think,
relate to that.

00:19:59.670 --> 00:20:01.770 align:middle line:84%
And that's where I've said
to women, particularly,

00:20:01.770 --> 00:20:03.870 align:middle line:84%
but it's true for men,
if the train doesn't

00:20:03.870 --> 00:20:07.020 align:middle line:84%
stop at your station, it's
because it's not your train.

00:20:07.020 --> 00:20:09.120 align:middle line:84%
We hold on to
relationships that aren't

00:20:09.120 --> 00:20:11.250 align:middle line:90%
blooming, aren't working.

00:20:11.250 --> 00:20:14.640 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes, it's because
the conductor of that train

00:20:14.640 --> 00:20:15.810 align:middle line:90%
is right.

00:20:15.810 --> 00:20:19.770 align:middle line:84%
His intuition or her intuition
is saying don't stop here.

00:20:19.770 --> 00:20:21.540 align:middle line:84%
But our intensity is
delaying-- don't go!

00:20:21.540 --> 00:20:22.340 align:middle line:90%
Don't go!

00:20:22.340 --> 00:20:22.950 align:middle line:90%
Don't go!

00:20:22.950 --> 00:20:23.740 align:middle line:90%
Don't go!

00:20:23.740 --> 00:20:25.198 align:middle line:84%
And of course, the
tragedy there is

00:20:25.198 --> 00:20:27.757 align:middle line:84%
there is another train trying
to get into your station,

00:20:27.757 --> 00:20:29.340 align:middle line:84%
would get into your
station, but can't

00:20:29.340 --> 00:20:31.048 align:middle line:84%
get into your station
because of this one

00:20:31.048 --> 00:20:33.390 align:middle line:84%
that doesn't even belong
there anymore is delayed.

00:20:33.390 --> 00:20:35.280 align:middle line:90%
>> It's still in your station.

00:20:35.280 --> 00:20:40.750 align:middle line:84%
>> So this idea of detaching,
it's a hard area to detach

00:20:40.750 --> 00:20:41.550 align:middle line:90%
from.

00:20:41.550 --> 00:20:43.380 align:middle line:84%
It's a very difficult
area to say,

00:20:43.380 --> 00:20:46.350 align:middle line:84%
"Dear God, it's in
your hands, whatever."

00:20:46.350 --> 00:20:48.870 align:middle line:84%
But if we can, it's like
any other area of life.

00:20:48.870 --> 00:20:51.582 align:middle line:84%
If you can give it over
to the flow of something

00:20:51.582 --> 00:20:53.040 align:middle line:84%
with a greater
wisdom and a greater

00:20:53.040 --> 00:20:56.880 align:middle line:84%
kind of cosmic intelligence
than your ego thinking,

00:20:56.880 --> 00:20:58.440 align:middle line:90%
we can have it all.

00:20:58.440 --> 00:21:00.690 align:middle line:84%
>> But I've heard men say,
"I know she's going to come

00:21:00.690 --> 00:21:05.120 align:middle line:84%
around, because I'm just
waiting for her to grow up."

00:21:05.120 --> 00:21:06.182 align:middle line:90%
Should we wait?

00:21:06.182 --> 00:21:07.640 align:middle line:84%
>> I think every
case is different.

00:21:07.640 --> 00:21:10.043 align:middle line:84%
And I can't tell a person
what they're supposed to do.

00:21:10.043 --> 00:21:11.960 align:middle line:10%
You can't judge those
things from the outside.

00:21:11.960 --> 00:21:13.820 align:middle line:10%
I think God tells
us those things.

00:21:13.820 --> 00:21:16.460 align:middle line:10%
Sometimes the lesson in a
relationship is hang in there.

00:21:16.460 --> 00:21:18.230 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes the lesson
in a relationship

00:21:18.230 --> 00:21:20.060 align:middle line:90%
is learn to let go.

00:21:20.060 --> 00:21:21.742 align:middle line:90%
Every relationship is different.

00:21:21.742 --> 00:21:23.450 align:middle line:84%
That's why it's so
important to meditate.

00:21:23.450 --> 00:21:25.130 align:middle line:84%
That's why it's so
important to pray

00:21:25.130 --> 00:21:28.190 align:middle line:84%
so that we can get clear about
what a higher wisdom is really

00:21:28.190 --> 00:21:29.720 align:middle line:90%
saying to us.

00:21:29.720 --> 00:21:32.740 align:middle line:84%
>> If you could sum up
your whole book, Marianne,

00:21:32.740 --> 00:21:36.180 align:middle line:84%
in about a minute, and there's
somebody out there who needs

00:21:36.180 --> 00:21:39.020 align:middle line:84%
some help right now,
what would you say?

00:21:39.020 --> 00:21:40.490 align:middle line:90%
What is this book about?

00:21:40.490 --> 00:21:42.590 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that there
is an inner room,

00:21:42.590 --> 00:21:44.450 align:middle line:90%
kind of like a romantic chakra.

00:21:44.450 --> 00:21:45.260 align:middle line:90%
It's a temple.

00:21:45.260 --> 00:21:48.060 align:middle line:90%
It's like a romantic temple.

00:21:48.060 --> 00:21:51.750 align:middle line:84%
And I think it dwells in all
of us, at least in potential.

00:21:51.750 --> 00:21:54.620 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's like any
other temple space inside.

00:21:54.620 --> 00:21:57.780 align:middle line:84%
If we knock on it, then
the door will open.

00:21:57.780 --> 00:21:59.410 align:middle line:90%
And we can go in there.

00:21:59.410 --> 00:22:03.930 align:middle line:84%
And if we go in there
and allow the love that

00:22:03.930 --> 00:22:07.920 align:middle line:84%
is in there enter
into us and renew us,

00:22:07.920 --> 00:22:09.750 align:middle line:84%
then sooner than
we have any idea,

00:22:09.750 --> 00:22:12.117 align:middle line:90%
someone will join us in there.

00:22:12.117 --> 00:22:13.950 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think if you
really want somebody,

00:22:13.950 --> 00:22:14.750 align:middle line:90%
you can have them?

00:22:14.750 --> 00:22:17.042 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, not necessarily the
person you think you want?

00:22:17.042 --> 00:22:18.240 align:middle line:90%
>> Not person, but a person.

00:22:18.240 --> 00:22:19.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:22:19.040 --> 00:22:22.440 align:middle line:84%
I think that if love, if
intimate love and partnership,

00:22:22.440 --> 00:22:27.750 align:middle line:84%
with a beloved is the
highest growth for our souls,

00:22:27.750 --> 00:22:30.150 align:middle line:84%
then it's reaching out for
us and the real issue becomes

00:22:30.150 --> 00:22:32.220 align:middle line:90%
how receptive we are.

00:22:32.220 --> 00:22:36.840 align:middle line:84%
>> And can we tell that by
how strong our longing is?

00:22:36.840 --> 00:22:38.250 align:middle line:90%
>> I don't know.

00:22:38.250 --> 00:22:40.188 align:middle line:84%
I think that our longing
for another person

00:22:40.188 --> 00:22:41.730 align:middle line:84%
as "The Course of
Miracles" says it's

00:22:41.730 --> 00:22:44.190 align:middle line:90%
a shadow of our longing for God.

00:22:44.190 --> 00:22:46.410 align:middle line:84%
I think it's part of
our journey to God.

00:22:46.410 --> 00:22:48.030 align:middle line:90%
I think it's a great mystery.

00:22:48.030 --> 00:22:51.150 align:middle line:84%
But I think that if we embark on
a deeper conversation with God

00:22:51.150 --> 00:22:53.730 align:middle line:84%
about it, not just, "Dear
God, send me somebody,"

00:22:53.730 --> 00:22:55.260 align:middle line:84%
but "Dear God, show
me what it means

00:22:55.260 --> 00:22:57.600 align:middle line:84%
to be on a sacred
romantic adventure,"

00:22:57.600 --> 00:23:00.300 align:middle line:84%
then I think the answers
come more than we know.

00:23:00.300 --> 00:23:01.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you are a
marvelous answer.

00:23:01.910 --> 00:23:02.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:23:02.710 --> 00:23:04.170 align:middle line:90%
>> We've been privileged today--

00:23:04.170 --> 00:23:04.830 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

